el=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_open', tag='p', nesting=1, attrs={}, map=[670, 671], level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='inline', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=[670, 671], level=1, children=[Token(type='text', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content="Although simple, the single-project monolithic solution has some disadvantages. As the project's size and complexity grows, the number of files and folders will continue to grow as well. User interface (UI) concerns (models, views, controllers) reside in multiple folders, which aren't grouped together alphabetically. This issue only gets worse when additional UI-level constructs, such as Filters or ModelBinders, are added in their own folders. Business logic is scattered between the Models and Services folders, and there's no clear indication of which classes in which folders should depend on which others. This lack of organization at the project level frequently leads to spaghetti code .", markup='', info='', meta={}, block=False, hidden=False)], content="Although simple, the single-project monolithic solution has some disadvantages. As the project's size and complexity grows, the number of files and folders will continue to grow as well. User interface (UI) concerns (models, views, controllers) reside in multiple folders, which aren't grouped together alphabetically. This issue only gets worse when additional UI-level constructs, such as Filters or ModelBinders, are added in their own folders. Business logic is scattered between the Models and Services folders, and there's no clear indication of which classes in which folders should depend on which others. This lack of organization at the project level frequently leads to spaghetti code .", markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_close', tag='p', nesting=-1, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_open', tag='p', nesting=1, attrs={}, map=[672, 673], level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='inline', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=[672, 673], level=1, children=[Token(type='text', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='To address these issues, applications often evolve into multi-project solutions, where each project is considered to reside in a particular layer of the application.', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=False, hidden=False)], content='To address these issues, applications often evolve into multi-project solutions, where each project is considered to reside in a particular layer of the application.', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_close', tag='p', nesting=-1, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='heading_open', tag='h2', nesting=1, attrs={}, map=[674, 675], level=0, children=None, content='', markup='##', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='inline', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=[674, 675], level=1, children=[Token(type='text', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='What are layers?', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=False, hidden=False)], content='What are layers?', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='heading_close', tag='h2', nesting=-1, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='', markup='##', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_open', tag='p', nesting=1, attrs={}, map=[676, 677], level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='inline', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=[676, 677], level=1, children=[Token(type='text', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='As applications grow in complexity, one way to manage that complexity is to break up the application according to its responsibilities or concerns. This approach follows the separation of concerns principle and can help keep a growing codebase organized so that developers can easily find where certain functionality is implemented. Layered architecture offers a number of advantages beyond just code organization, though.', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=False, hidden=False)], content='As applications grow in complexity, one way to manage that complexity is to break up the application according to its responsibilities or concerns. This approach follows the separation of concerns principle and can help keep a growing codebase organized so that developers can easily find where certain functionality is implemented. Layered architecture offers a number of advantages beyond just code organization, though.', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_close', tag='p', nesting=-1, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_open', tag='p', nesting=1, attrs={}, map=[678, 679], level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='inline', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=[678, 679], level=1, children=[Token(type='text', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content="By organizing code into layers, common low-level functionality can be reused throughout the application. This reuse is beneficial because it means less code needs to be written and because it can allow the application to standardize on a single implementation, following the don't repeat yourself (DRY) principle.", markup='', info='', meta={}, block=False, hidden=False)], content="By organizing code into layers, common low-level functionality can be reused throughout the application. This reuse is beneficial because it means less code needs to be written and because it can allow the application to standardize on a single implementation, following the don't repeat yourself (DRY) principle.", markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_close', tag='p', nesting=-1, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_open', tag='p', nesting=1, attrs={}, map=[680, 681], level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='inline', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=[680, 681], level=1, children=[Token(type='text', tag='', nesting=0, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content="With a layered architecture, applications can enforce restrictions on which layers can communicate with other layers. This architecture helps to achieve encapsulation. When a layer is changed or replaced, only those layers that work with it should be impacted. By limiting which layers depend on which other layers, the impact of changes can be mitigated so that a single change doesn't impact the entire application.", markup='', info='', meta={}, block=False, hidden=False)], content="With a layered architecture, applications can enforce restrictions on which layers can communicate with other layers. This architecture helps to achieve encapsulation. When a layer is changed or replaced, only those layers that work with it should be impacted. By limiting which layers depend on which other layers, the impact of changes can be mitigated so that a single change doesn't impact the entire application.", markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_close', tag='p', nesting=-1, attrs={}, map=None, level=0, children=None, content='', markup='', info='', meta={}, block=True, hidden=False), Token(type='paragraph_open', tag='p', n